" Everything has been done to cover the economy and ordinary Americans in the face of the current crisis on Wall Street, " the Democrat explained.
" It's the fundamental point: if we don't do this, trauma, chaos and disruptions to the daily lives of Americans will be immense, " declared Republican Judd Gregg.
Negotiations had ended very quickly in the last few hours because they feared the effect of a further failure on the mood of investors.
The last hour that had been set was the opening of the markets this morning.
