"We must break the vicious circle of poverty, segregation and unemployment, we must offer Gypsy children the possibility that guarantees the democratic space so that they can contribute to the future of Europe as citizens of full rights," Járóka demanded.
The objective of the European Summit for Equal Opportunities, organised annually since last year's Berlin meeting in the "European Year of Equal Opportunities", is to ensure a unique forum to promote the abolition of discrimination and equal opportunities at European and national level in the Member States.
