Listening to high volume music for a long time using portable musical devices like Mp3 readers can cause permanent hearing injuries.
It is the European Commission's point that in a press release in Brussels it cites the opinion of the Scientific Commission on the Emerging and Recently Identified Health Risk (Csrseri) of the EU, published today.
"From this scientific opinion – it is read in the note – it appears that 5-10% of those who, for a period of at least 5 years, listen to music with portable musical devices weekly for more than an hour a day having the apparatus at high volume risk a permanent loss of hearing capacity."
